			<tr>
				<td colspan="2" height="100%" valign="top"><span class="postbody"><h3>Instructions</h3>
<br />
<ul><li><font color="red"><b>Please complete your application in notepad or Word so that you don't lose your work when trying to post it! Once you've got it all together, then you can paste it into a new message on this forum.</b></font>
<br />

<br />
<li><b>Incomplete applications won't be considered</b>. If you can't fill this application properly (it's easier than a McDonalds application for third-shift fry cook, as verified by a genuine McDonalds third-shift fry cook!) then you'll probably fail to follow directions on a raid, too. Do it right or go find a guild short on raid disicipline and long on corpse recovery practice.</b></font>
<br />

<br />
<li><b>Requirements</b>: We're looking for people who know their class well, have a sense of humor, are good communicators, want more out of the game than just another zerg raid, and who have the patience to help us grow Science of War into a top guild serverwide. We're recruiting players who are on Stormhammer for the long term. 
<br />

<br />
Though you can apply <b>before</b> you meet the requirements below, to be <b>accepted</b> to the guild, you must: 
<br />
<ul>
<br />
<li>be 17 years of age or older
<br />
<li>have all EQ expansions activated
<br />
<li>have 200 sense heading and swimming skill
<br />
<li>have your own means of shrinking and invising
<br />
<li>have at least one insta-case clickable buff item 
<br />
<li>be unguilded (this includes all of your scurvy alts)
<br />
<li>be level 64 or above if you're a cleric, and level 65 if you're not a cleric
<br />
<li><font color="red">new</font>: at least have your first AA title (Baron / Baroness) including Run3.
<br />
<li>have the pouch, idol and ring needed for the <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=1999">Ring of the Shissar key quest</a>
<br />
<li>have at least eight out of ten shards needed for the VT key quest
<br />
<li>be able to enter PoS, PoV, BoT, and PoNb
<br />
<li>You must be available to raid between the hours of 8pm ET and 12am ET at least four days per week
<br />
</ul>
<br />

<br />
</ol>
<br />
<h3>The Application</h3>
<br />
<hr>
<br />
<ol>
<br />
<li>Name, Level, Race, Class, Server of Origin:
<br />
<li>If you've had your name changed, list all previous names:
<br />
<li><a href="http://www.magelo.com">Magelo</a> Profile URL. (Doublecheck your AC/HP. Make a resist profile too.) 
<br />
<li>Enter your magelo into <a href="http://www.eqrankings.com/?rm=overview&class=">this tool</a>. Tell us your rank in terms of HP, Mana, AC, and AA points against ALL members of your class on all servers. 
<br />
<li>How many AA do you have and where did you spend the points?
<br />
<li>Do you have your <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=1999">emperor ring</a>? If not, what parts do you have? What are you doing to complete your ring?
<br />
<li>What keys and PoP Flags do you hold?
<br />
<li>Names and levels of alts that you play and the servers they're on:
<br />
<li>(For casters) What spells are you MISSING from level 50 to 65?
<br />
<li>(For melee only) Do you have a <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=1998">Shissar bane weapon</a>? If not, how do you plan to get one?
<br />
<li>Which VT key-quest shards do you possess?
<br />
<li>What are your goals for your character in the next six months?
<br />
<li>Your timezone:
<br />
<li>What hours do you play each day? How many total hours per week?
<br />
<li>Did a SoW member ask you to apply? If so, who? 
<br />
<li>Do you have a permanent enduring breath item? Spells don't count.
<br />
<li>Do you have an instant-buff item that works indoors (example: shrunken goblin skull earring)?
<br />
<li>What are you looking for in a guild? Why Science of War?
<br />
<li>What is your guild history on your old server and on Stormhammer? 
<br />
<li>Why did you leave your previous guild(s)?
<br />
<li>Why did you move to Stormhammer? When do you plan to leave, if at all?
<br />

<br />
<li><b>The test of humor</b>: Be creative and have fun with this one! Basically we ask you post something humorous. A joke. A screenshot. A flatbed scan of your ass.
<br />

<br />
<li><b>Test of Strategy</b>: Go to the online text of "The Art of War" by Sun Tzu at <a href="http://www.sonshi.com/learn.html" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://www.sonshi.com/learn.html</a> and select one to four lines of text for interpretation. Explain what that text means in the context of the Everquest experience. Post your quote and your interpretation here:
<br />

<br />
<li><b>The test of knowledge</b>: Choose ONE of the following three questions. 
<br />

<br />
<b>(Option A)</b> Answer the following questions about your class <i>in detail</i>. (1) Rank the following stats in order of importance for your class and explain WHY you ranked them that way. HP, AC, mana, mana regeneration, HP regeneration, attack, INT, STA, STR, WIS, DEX, CHA, AGI, level, MR, FR, CR, PR, DR. (2) What stats does the TOP player of your class (serverwide) have? (No need to be exact, just give us a ballpark figure.) (3) What are the top five mistakes that BAD players of your class make?
<br />

<br />
<b>(Option B)</b> We are a Tier 8 guild. This means that we are capable of all Velious and Shadows of Luclin Content (including VT). We are focused on raiding Ssra and VT, and have begun to advance in PoP. Critique your magelo, piece by piece, and suggest one upgrade per slot, but do not suggest upgrades that are not within our raid focus.
<br />

<br />
<b>(Option C)</b> Post a class-specific "guide" to a class board. For instance, monks might post a "Guide to Pulling King Tormax" to <a href="http://www.monkly-business.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">www.monkly-business.com</a>. Shaman might post a "Guide to Curse Removal" to <a href="http://www.eqshaman.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">www.eqshaman.com</a>, Enchanters might post a list of "Dire Charmable Mobs, Organized by Zone" and so on. Once you have posted your guide, paste the URL here:</ol>
<br />

<br />
Post your application to the application forum then read up on <a href="http://www.scienceofwar.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=82">the application decision process</a>.</span><br /><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by soupypoopy on 07.02 12.11am, edited 1 time in total</span></td>
			</tr>
